<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The cast-to-void statement `(void) cls;` is an executed, effect-free operation whose removal would not change program behaviour. It merely silences a compiler warning about an unused parameter and has no runtime effect, so it constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. A compliant alternative is to omit the parameter name in the function signature or use a standardized mechanism to mark the parameter as intentionally unused (e.g. a compiler attribute), rather than leaving an effect-free expression statement.
</scenario>

